.TH "RK\-VIM\-VISUAL Reference" "" "" ""
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]⌃v\f[R]: Visual Block Mode
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]gv\f[R]: Reselect last visual block
.SS Blocks
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]vip\f[R]: Select paragraph
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]va{V\f[R]: Select current function
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]V$%\f[R]: More reliable way to select current function
.SS Notes
Text cut with \f[CR]\(hav\f[R] or \f[CR]v\f[R] is \f[CR]blockwise\f[R],
if you then paste it, the text will interleave with any lines it
overlaps with.
To get around this behavior, just use the \f[CR]:put\f[R] command, which
pastes the text as if it were yanked \f[CR]linewise\f[R].
.SS Visual Block Mode
Easy to edit before and after the selection:
.IP "1." 3
\f[CR]C\-v\f[R]: Start the selection
.IP "2." 3
\f[CR]hjkl\f[R]: Select the relevant text
.SH Inserting Text Before / After Selection
Use \f[CR]I\f[R] or \f[CR]A\f[R] to insert text at the beginning or end
of the selection
.SH Examples
.SS Deleting
.IP \(bu 2
Delete text from the beginning of the line by starting a block selection
(\f[CR]C\-v\f[R]) then selecting the text, then hitting \f[CR]x\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
Delete text from the end of the line from a specific column by starting
a block selection (\f[CR]C\-v\f[R]) from where to delete from, then
going to the last line to perform the delete on, then \f[CR]$\f[R] to go
to the end of the line, then \f[CR]x\f[R] to delete
.SS Pasting
.IP \(bu 2
Paste a column of text after another column of text by performing a
delete (\f[CR]x\f[R]) or yank (\f[CR]y\f[R]) after a block selection
(\f[CR]C\-v\f[R]) (in order to assure the yanked text is a
\f[CR]blockwise\f[R] itself [otherwise it will all be inserted into a
single line]) on the text to paste, then performing another block
selection on the lines to paste too, then going to the end of the line
(\f[CR]$\f[R]), then pasting (\f[CR]p\f[R])
.IP \(bu 2
It\(cqs impossible to insert a \f[CR]blockwise\f[R] selection to the
ends of lines that aren\(cqt the same length (as an alternative use the
shell command \f[CR]col\f[R] then work with tab\-delimited columns)
